First review ever. This is the only Starbucks that has continuously ruined my orders.  Today I clarified the order before paying because the cashier was confused (I order the same thing everywhere, no issues). After they messed it up the first time and I politely told them what I wanted, they made the same drink again.  I did not have time to correct them again, I had to get back to work.  This is not the first time they have butchered simple orders, I will not be going back.

I'm not a coffee drinker, so my experience st Starbucks is likely very different than the typical customer. When I go there it is typically out of necessity, like I'm traveling for business and Starbucks is the place I can setup for some breakfast on my way to the office I'm visiting. I find their food to be what if expect from a coffee shop. It is adequate and of decent quality. Same with the hot chocolate I usually get. It's hot and adequate, though nothing I'll write home about. I have no complaints about the service or experience, but also nothing to rave about.
